<p itemprop="description">A lead content designer leads the content design function across the organisation, setting strategic direction for content practices and ensuring user-centred content approaches are embedded throughout all digital services. They manage content design teams and drive organisational content strategy.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Define and implement content design strategy across the entire organisation</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead and manage content design teams and specialists</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish content design governance, standards, and best practices</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Champion user-centred content approaches at executive level</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Build strategic partnerships with content and design communities</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Oversee content design capability development and training programmes</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive innovation in content design tools, techniques, and methodologies</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Ensure content design excellence across all organisational programmes</li>
    </ul>
</section>

